&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m using a similar setup, but wanted to add some stuff I personally find very useful:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;nodemon (nodemon.io): start your node server with &#039;nodemon&#039; instead of &#039;node&#039; and it will automatically restart whenever a file changes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Oh My Zsh: a replacement for the standard OS X Terminal, making it easier to work with (that should get your attention :-) I like the color coding and that it only shows the current folder (not a full hierarchy).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Useful Sublime Text plugins (installed via Package Manager - the Sublime Text package manager):&lt;br /&gt;  - Sublime Linter with the JSHint plugin for Javascript validation&lt;br /&gt;  - Bracket Highlighter (highlights brackets)&lt;br /&gt;  - Side Bar Enhancements: add right click options to files (for instance &#034;run in browser&#034;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
